  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Dopamine agonists, such as quinagolide, are able to act on the VEGFR-2 blocking antibodies,
      diminishing Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor effect on angiogenesis in human endometriotic
      lesions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
